h3cIfExt.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip: 100085
h3cIfExt.description: This MIB is an extension of interface MIBs such as IF-MIB. This MIB is applicable to routers, switches and other products. Some objects in this may be used only for some specific products, so users should refer to the related documents to acquire more detail information.

h3cRTParentIfTable.name: h3cRTParentIfTable
h3cRTParentIfTable.description: This table contains all interfaces that can create sub interface.

h3cRTParentIfEntry.name: h3cRTParentIfEntry
h3cRTParentIfEntry.description: This entry describes a interface that can create sub interface.

h3cRTParentIfIndex.name: h3cRTParentIfIndex
h3cRTParentIfIndex.description: The index of interface that can creat sub interface. The value is the same as ifIndex value for this interface.

h3cRTMinSubIfOrdinal.name: h3cRTMinSubIfOrdinal
h3cRTMinSubIfOrdinal.description: The minimum ordinal of the sub interface can be created.

h3cRTMaxSubIfOrdinal.name: h3cRTMaxSubIfOrdinal
h3cRTMaxSubIfOrdinal.description: The max ordinal of the sub interface can be created.

h3cRTSubIfTable.name: h3cRTSubIfTable
h3cRTSubIfTable.description: This table contains objects to create or delete sub interfaces. To create a sub interface, a valid parent interface must be specified by h3cRTSubIfParentIfIndex and the h3cRTSubIfOrdinal must be in the range between h3cRTMinSubIfOrdinal and h3cRTMaxSubIfOrdinal of the parent interface from h3cRTParentIfTable. Sub interfaces are logical virtual interfaces configured on a main interface. The main interface can be either a physical interface (such as a Layer 3 Ethernet interface) or a logical interface (such as an MFR interface). The subinterfaces on a main interface share the physical layer parameters of the main interface but can have link layer and network layer parameters of their own. Disabling or enabling a subinterface does not affect the main interface, but the main interface status change affects the subinterfaces. The subinterfaces cannot operate normally unless the main interface is connected. A single physical interface containing multiple subinterfaces enables you to network in a more flexible way. You can create subinterfaces for the following physical interfaces: Ethernet interface. An Ethernet subinterface associated with no VLAN supports only IPX, while an Ethernet subinterface associated with a VLAN supports both IP and IPX. WAN interfaces with their data link layer protocols being frame relay, whose subinterfaces support IP and IPX. WAN interfaces with their data link layer protocols being X.25, whose subinterfaces support IP and IPX. ATM interface, whose subinterfaces support only IP.

h3cRTSubIfParentIfIndex.name: h3cRTSubIfParentIfIndex
h3cRTSubIfParentIfIndex.description: The parent interface index. The value should be the same as the h3cRTParentIfIndex.

h3cRTSubIfOrdinal.name: h3cRTSubIfOrdinal
h3cRTSubIfOrdinal.description: The ordinal of sub interface. It should between h3cRTMinSubIfOrdinal and h3cRTMaxSubIfOrdinal of the parent interface.

h3cRTSubIfSubIfIndex.name: h3cRTSubIfSubIfIndex
h3cRTSubIfSubIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the sub interface

h3cIfLinkModeTable.name: h3cIfLinkModeTable
h3cIfLinkModeTable.description: This table contains objects to get or set the link mode of an interface. According to the layer at which the device processes received data packets, Ethernet interfaces can operate in bridge or route mode.

h3cIfLinkModeEntry.name: h3cIfLinkModeEntry
h3cIfLinkModeEntry.description: The interface link mode table entry

h3cIfLinkModeIndex.name: h3cIfLinkModeIndex
h3cIfLinkModeIndex.description: The value is same as ifIndex.

h3cIfLinkMode.name: h3cIfLinkMode
h3cIfLinkMode.description: The current link mode of the interface If h3cIfLinkModeSwitchSupport is true, writing to the object can change the link mode of the interface.

h3cIfLinkModeSwitchSupport.name: h3cIfLinkModeSwitchSupport
h3cIfLinkModeSwitchSupport.description: Whether the interface supports link mode switching. If this object is true, the interface can operate in either bridge mode or route mode. Otherwise the interfaces can operate only in bridge or route mode.

h3cIfPhysicalNumber.name: h3cIfPhysicalNumber
h3cIfPhysicalNumber.description: Represents the number of physical interfaces in the device.

h3cIfTable.name: h3cIfTable
h3cIfTable.description: A list of interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of IfNumber.

h3cIfEntry.name: h3cIfEntry
h3cIfEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular interface.

h3cIfUpDownTimes.name: h3cIfUpDownTimes
h3cIfUpDownTimes.description: The interface's up/down times, since the device was initialized.

h3cIfMtu.name: h3cIfMtu
h3cIfMtu.description: The size of the largest datagram which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets. For interfaces that are used for transmitting network datagram, this is the size of the largest network datagram that can be sent on the interface.

h3cIfBandwidthRate.name: h3cIfBandwidthRate
h3cIfBandwidthRate.description: The rate of the bandwidth for an interface.

h3cIfDiscardPktRate.name: h3cIfDiscardPktRate
h3cIfDiscardPktRate.description: The rate of the discarded packets for an interface.

h3cIfStatusKeepTime.name: h3cIfStatusKeepTime
h3cIfStatusKeepTime.description: The time since the interface entered its current operational state.

h3cIfInNUcastPkts.name: h3cIfInNUcastPkts
h3cIfInNUcastPkts.description: The number of non-unicast (i.e., subnetwork- broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

h3cIfOutNUcastPkts.name: h3cIfOutNUcastPkts
h3cIfOutNUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a non- unicast (i.e., a subnetwork-broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) address.

h3cIfBandwidthUsageHigh.name: h3cIfBandwidthUsageHigh
h3cIfBandwidthUsageHigh.description: The notification is generated when the rate of the bandwidth for the interface exceeds the upper limit.

h3cIfDiscardPktRateHigh.name: h3cIfDiscardPktRateHigh
h3cIfDiscardPktRateHigh.description: The notification is generated when the rate of the discarded packets for the interface exceeds the upper limit.

h3cIfBandwidthUpperLimit.name: h3cIfBandwidthUpperLimit
h3cIfBandwidthUpperLimit.description: The rate of the bandwidth upper limit for an interface.

h3cIfDiscardPktRateUpperLimit.name: h3cIfDiscardPktRateUpperLimit
h3cIfDiscardPktRateUpperLimit.description: The rate of the discarded packets upper limit for an interface.
